SIMPLE: snowflake
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snowflake
<hw>Snow"flake`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
flake, or small filmy mass, of snow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>See <er>Snowbird</er>,
1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A name given to several bulbous
plants of the genus <gen>Leucoium</gen> (<spn>Leucoium vernum</spn>,
<spn>Leucoium aestivum</spn>, etc.) resembling the snowdrop, but having
all the perianth leaves of equal size.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snowfleck</ent>⟦br⟧
